<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/blasphemy">Blasphemy</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180923061905/https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/blasphemy">Archived</a> 23 September 2018 at the <a href="/wiki/Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a> Merriam Webster (July 2013); 1. great disrespect shown to God or to something holy<br />2. irreverence toward something considered sacred or inviolable</span>
